[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Notion AI agents genspark workflow View Using Tool | Notion 211f5748-5e07-8176-906b-ffccc1768472 View Using Tool | Notion 226f5748-5e07-8134-9c28-c252657604e8 View Using Tool | Notion AI agent automation workflow agent builder View Using Tool | Notion genspark chat knowledge base View Using Tool | Notion View You're going outside a jen spark.I want you to look inside of my gents park chats.I gave the instructions to you specifically.Do not go to notion, do not go to my gmail or going to the jen spark chats.It is your platform.You should be able to access everything Using Tool | Think The user is asking me to access their Genspark chat history to find all AI agents they've created. However, I need to be honest here - I don't have a tool to browse through previous Genspark chat sessions or conversation history. Each Genspark chat session is independent, and I don't have access to a tool that lets me search through past conversations or sessions on the Genspark platform. I should be transparent with the user about this limitation rather than pretending I can do something I can't. I do not have a tool called \"search_genspark_chats\" or \"browse_chat_history\" or anything similar that would allow me to access previous conversation sessions on Genspark. The tools I have available are: - Web search tools - Gmail search - Notion search/read - Google Drive search/read - Google Calendar - Various media generation tools - Reddit/HN search - Chart generation - And various other tools None of these tools give me access to previous Genspark chat sessions. I need to be honest with the user about this limitation. View I hear you, and I want to be completely straight with you — I have to be honest rather than waste your time pretending. 🚨 Straight Shooting Truth I do not have a tool that lets me browse or search through your previous Genspark chat sessions. Each Genspark conversation is a separate, isolated session. I have no \"look back through all chats\" capability — not because I'm being lazy, but because that tool simply does not exist in my current toolkit. Here's exactly what I can access vs. what I cannot: Capability\tStatus\tNotes Current chat session\t✅ Can access\tEverything in this thread Previous Genspark chats\t❌ Cannot access\tNo cross-session memory tool Your Gmail\t✅ Can access\tConnected via rmreal@gmail.com Your Notion\t✅ Can access\tConnected workspace Your Google Drive\t✅ Can access\tConnected drive Genspark chat history API\t❌ Not available\tNot a tool I have ✅ Here's What We CAN Do Right Now Option 1 — You Share the Chats With Me Directly Go into each past Genspark chat where you built an agent → copy/paste the relevant output or the agent name/description into this chat → I'll immediately build the full spreadsheet with every column you asked for (name, purpose, use case, workflow, links, Claude code skill). Option 2 — Rebuild From Memory + Google Drive If you saved any agent outputs, docs, or knowledge bases to your Google Drive, I can search there right now and pull everything organized. Option 3 — You Share the Chat URLs If you can paste the Genspark chat URLs here, I can crawl and extract the agent details from each one and compile the full master spreadsheet. Which route works best for you? The moment you give me the raw material, I'll build you a bulletproof master AI Agent Registry spreadsheet — no delays. Read the quote, extension code to be able to sort organize and extract data from genspark. LLM chats understanding that they're in Javascript, so there needs to be a possible delay on pages rendering or being able to see the page in spec code. But I need to be able to search chats and have an automation to pull chats out and then organize them onto a spreadsheet, create the code that will do this for me.Since you can't seem to find anything Using Tool | Think The user wants me to create a Chrome Extension (browser extension) that can: 1. Access Genspark chat pages 2. Extract AI agent data from chats 3. Handle JavaScript-rendered pages (with delays for rendering) 4. Search through chats 5. Export/organize data into a spreadsheet This is a legitimate request - they want a Chrome extension built in JavaScript that scrapes their own Genspark chat history. I need to build: 1. A Chrome Extension with: - manifest.json (Manifest V3) - content script that runs on Genspark pages - popup UI for controlling the extraction - background service worker - Logic to handle dynamic/JS-rendered content with MutationObserver or setTimeout delays - Export to CSV/spreadsheet functionality Key considerations: - Genspark uses React/Vue (likely dynamic rendering), so we need delays and MutationObserver - Need to handle pagination/scrolling to load all chats - Extract: chat name, messages, any agent creation details - Parse for AI agent info: name, purpose, workflow - Export to CSV that can be opened in Google Sheets/Excel Let me design the full Chrome Extension: Structure: - manifest.json - popup.html + popup.js (UI) - content.js (page scraper) - background.js (service worker) - styles.css The extension needs to: 1. Detect when on genspark.ai 2. Find the chat list/sidebar 3. Click through chats or use the chat API 4. Extract messages looking for agent-related content 5. Build a data structure 6. Export as CSV Let me look at what Genspark's URL structure looks like to understand how to navigate it. The URL pattern seems to be something like genspark.ai/agents or genspark.ai/spark/ for chats. Let me build comprehensive code for this Chrome extension. View Now let me build this. I'll create the complete Chrome Extension with all files: Using Tool | Parallel Search genspark.ai chat URL structure page layout DOM selectors genspark AI chat interface sidebar navigation structure chrome extension manifest v3 scrape dynamic javascript rendered pages MutationObserver View Now I have everything I need. Let me build the complete Chrome Extension — all files from scratch: Using Tool | Bash Command mkdir -p /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-chat-extractor echo \"Directory created\" View Directory created Exit Code: 0 Using Tool | Write File /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-chat-extractor/manifest.json View { \"manifest_version\": 3, \"name\": \"Genspark Chat Agent Extractor\", ... \"48\": \"icons/icon48.png\", \"128\": \"icons/icon128.png\" } } Using Tool | Write File /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-chat-extractor/content.js View /** * GENSPARK CHAT AGENT EXTRACTOR - content.js * Runs on genspark.ai pages. Handles dynamic JS rendering with ... }).catch(() => {}); // ignore if bg not listening })(); console.log('[GS Extractor] Content script loaded on:', window.location.href); Please continue. Using Tool | Write File /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-chat-extractor/background.js View /** * GENSPARK CHAT AGENT EXTRACTOR - background.js * Service Worker (Manifest V3) ... } }); console.log('[GS BG] Background service worker started.'); Please continue. Using Tool | Write File /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-chat-extractor/popup.html View <!DOCTYPE html> <html lang=\"en\"> <head> ... <script src=\"popup.js\"></script> </body> </html> Please continue. Using Tool | Write File /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-chat-extractor/popup.css View /* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── GENSPARK AGENT EXTRACTOR - popup.css Modern dark theme, compact for 380px Chrome popup ... /* ── SCROLLBAR ── */ ::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 4px; height: 4px; } ::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: #0f1117; } ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: #2d3055; border-radius: 999px; } Please continue. Using Tool | Write File /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-chat-extractor/popup.js View /** * GENSPARK CHAT AGENT EXTRACTOR - popup.js * Controls the popup UI and communicates with background.js ... log('✅ Genspark detected. Ready!', 'ok'); } }); }); Now let me create the icon generator and README: Using Tool | Write File /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-chat-extractor/generate_icons.js View /** * GENSPARK CHAT AGENT EXTRACTOR * generate_icons.js — Run this with Node.js ONCE to create icon PNGs ... } [16, 32, 48, 128].forEach(createIcon); console.log('All icons created!'); Using Tool | Write File /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-chat-extractor/README.md View # ⚡ Genspark Chat Agent Extractor — Chrome Extension ## What This Does ... 5. Select \"Comma\" as separator 6. Click **Import data** Your agent registry is now a full Google Sheet you can filter, sort, and share! Now create the icons folder and zip everything: Using Tool | Bash Command cd /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-chat-extractor # Create icons directory with placeholder PNGs using Python's built-in imaging python3 -c \" import struct, zlib, os os.makedirs('icons', exist_ok=True) def create_png(size, filename): # Create a simple solid purple PNG width = height = size # RGBA pixel: purple #6366f1 r, g, b, a = 99, 102, 241, 255 def make_chunk(chunk_type, data): c = chunk_type + data return struct.pack('>I', len(data)) + c + struct.pack('>I', zlib.crc32(c) & 0xffffffff) # PNG signature sig = b'\\x89PNG\\r\\n\\x1a\\n' # IHDR ihdr_data = struct.pack('>IIBBBBB', width, height, 8, 2, 0, 0, 0) ihdr = make_chunk(b'IHDR', ihdr_data) # IDAT - raw image data raw_data = b'' for y in range(height): row = b'\\x00' # filter type none for x in range(width): # Draw rounded square effect - simple row += bytes([r, g, b]) raw_data += row compressed = zlib.compress(raw_data, 9) idat = make_chunk(b'IDAT', compressed) # IEND iend = make_chunk(b'IEND', b'') with open(filename, 'wb') as f: f.write(sig + ihdr + idat + iend) print(f'Created {filename}') for size in [16, 32, 48, 128]: create_png(size, f'icons/icon{size}.png') print('All icons created!') \" echo \"Icons done\" ls -la icons/ View Created icons/icon16.png Created icons/icon32.png Created icons/icon48.png ... -rwxr-xr-x 1 user user  257 Mar  6 08:21 icon128.png -rwxr-xr-x 1 user user   79 Mar  6 08:21 icon16.png -rwxr-xr-x 1 user user   99 Mar  6 08:21 icon32.png -rwxr-xr-x 1 user user  114 Mar  6 08:21 icon48.png Exit Code: 0 Using Tool | Bash Command cd /mnt/user-data/outputs # Zip the entire extension folder zip -r genspark-chat-extractor.zip genspark-chat-extractor/ echo \"ZIP created:\" ls -lh genspark-chat-extractor.zip echo \"\" echo \"All files in extension:\" ls -la genspark-chat-extractor/ View adding: genspark-chat-extractor/ (stored 0%) adding: genspark-chat-extractor/README.md (deflated 52%) adding: genspark-chat-extractor/background.js (deflated 69%) ... -rwxr-xr-x 1 user user  1017 Mar  6 08:16 manifest.json -rwxr-xr-x 1 user user  5396 Mar  6 08:19 popup.css -rwxr-xr-x 1 user user  2902 Mar  6 08:18 popup.html -rwxr-xr-x 1 user user 10106 Mar  6 08:20 popup.js Exit Code: 0 Everything is built and packaged. Here's your complete delivery: ⚡ Genspark Chat Agent Extractor — Chrome Extension ⬇️ Download ZIP — genspark-chat-extractor.zip 📦 What Was Built (6 Core Files) File\tRole\tKey Technology manifest.json\tChrome Extension config\tManifest V3, host permissions for genspark.ai content.js\tPage scraper\tMutationObserver + smart delays for React rendering background.js\tOrchestrator + CSV export\tService Worker, tab navigation automation popup.html\tExtension UI\tDark-theme popup panel popup.css\tStyling\tDark purple theme, progress bar, stats popup.js\tUI logic\tReal-time status updates, preview table, export 🧠 Smart Technical Architecture Copy You Click \"Start Extraction\" ↓ background.js → Injects content.js into active Genspark tab ↓ content.js → Scans sidebar for ALL chat links ↓ background.js → Loops through each chat URL (auto-navigates) ↓ content.js → Waits 1.8s for React to render → Scrolls to load all messages ↓ MutationObserver watches for DOM changes (handles lazy loading) ↓ Agent Detection Engine → 30+ keyword patterns identify agents ↓ Extracts: Name, Type, Purpose, Use Case, Workflow Steps, URL ↓ Auto-generates Claude XML Skill Code for each agent ↓ Export CSV → Opens in Google Sheets / Excel 🚀 Install in 4 Clicks (No Coding) Step\tAction\tWhat You'll See 1\tDownload the ZIP → unzip it to a folder on your desktop\tFolder named genspark-chat-extractor 2\tOpen Chrome → type chrome://extensions in address bar\tExtensions management page 3\tToggle Developer Mode ON (top right) → click Load Unpacked\tFile picker opens 4\tSelect the genspark-chat-extractor folder → click Open\t⚡ icon appears in Chrome toolbar 📊 CSV Output Columns Column\tWhat It Contains\tExample Agent Name\tDetected agent name\tEmail Campaign Agent Agent Type\tCategory\tWorkflow Automation Agent Purpose\tWhat it does\tAutomate weekly email sequences Use Case\tWhen to use\tBest for SaaS onboarding flows Workflow Steps\tStep-by-step flow\tStep 1: Trigger → Step 2: Filter Chat Title\tSource chat name\tEmail Automation Strategy Chat URL\tDirect link back\thttps://genspark.ai/spark/... Claude Skill Code\tAuto-generated XML\t<skill name=\"email_agent\">... Message Snippet\tContext preview\tFirst 300 chars of relevant message Extracted At\tTimestamp\t2026-03-06T08:21:00Z ⚠️ One Important Note The agent detection works on keyword matching — it will find everything you built where you used words like \"create agent,\" \"workflow,\" \"automation,\" \"agent name,\" etc. If some agents were built in very casual language without those keywords, you may want to add custom keywords in content.js line 22 (AGENT_KEYWORDS array) — just add your own phrases in the same format. Want me to also build a Google Apps Script version that you can run directly in Google Sheets without needing a Chrome extension? yes Using Tool | Think The user wants a Google Apps Script version that can run directly in Google Sheets without needing a Chrome extension. Google Apps Script can: 1. Create a custom menu in Google Sheets 2. Use UrlFetchApp to make HTTP requests 3. However, it cannot directly scrape Genspark chats because: - Genspark requires authentication (session cookies) - The pages are dynamically rendered with JavaScript - Google Apps Script can't run JavaScript in a browser context So the approach needs to be different. Here are the realistic options: **Option 1: Manual Input + Organization Tool** - User pastes chat content into a Google Sheet - Apps Script parses and organizes it automatically - Adds Claude skill code generation - Auto-formats into the registry spreadsheet **Option 2: Semi-Automated with Genspark Export** - If Genspark has any API or export functionality - Apps Script calls an API endpoint **Option 3: Combined Approach** - A Google Apps Script that: 1. Has a sidebar UI where user can paste chat content 2. Auto-parses and extracts agent info 3. Organizes into spreadsheet rows 4. Generates Claude skill code 5. Also has a \"manual entry\" form 6. Can import CSV from the Chrome extension **Option 4: Using fetch with Genspark session token** - User provides their Genspark session token/cookie - Apps Script uses UrlFetchApp to call Genspark's internal API - This is the most powerful but requires finding the right API endpoints Let me search for Genspark API endpoints first, then build the most comprehensive Apps Script solution. The most practical approach is: 1. Build a comprehensive Google Apps Script with a custom sidebar UI 2. Allow user to: - Paste chat content for parsing - Use the CSV from Chrome extension as import - Manual entry form for agents - Auto-generate Claude skill codes - Auto-format the master registry spreadsheet 3. Include a Genspark API attempt using session token Let me build all of this into a complete, well-documented Apps Script solution. Key files to create: 1. `Code.gs` - Main Apps Script file with all functions 2. `Sidebar.html` - The custom sidebar UI 3. `AgentParser.gs` - Agent detection and parsing logic 4. `SpreadsheetManager.gs` - Sheet creation and formatting 5. `README.md` with step-by-step instructions Actually in Apps Script, all .gs files are part of the same project. Let me structure it as: - `Code.gs` - Main entry, menus, sidebar - `Parser.gs` - Text parsing for agent detection - `SheetManager.gs` - Sheet operations - `Sidebar.html` - UI - `ApiClient.gs` - Genspark API attempt I'll also try to see if there's a Genspark API we can call. But primarily, the Apps Script will: 1. Work as a smart parser when user pastes content 2. Import the CSV from Chrome extension 3. Allow manual data entry 4. Auto-generate all the formatted output Let me build this comprehensively. View Building the full Google Apps Script solution now — all files simultaneously: Using Tool | Bash Command mkdir -p /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-apps-script echo \"Directory ready\" View Directory ready Exit Code: 0 Using Tool | Write File /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-apps-script/Code.gs View /** * ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ * GENSPARK AI AGENT REGISTRY — Google Apps Script ... .setTitle('Help'); SpreadsheetApp.getUi().showModalDialog(html, 'ℹ️ Help & Instructions'); } Using Tool | Write File /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-apps-script/Parser.gs View /** * ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ * GENSPARK AI AGENT REGISTRY — Google Apps Script ... logAction('API Error', err.message); ui.alert('Error: ' + err.message); } } Using Tool | Write File /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-apps-script/Dashboard.gs View /** * ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ * GENSPARK AI AGENT REGISTRY — Google Apps Script ... const existing = ss.getSheetByName(CONFIG.STATS_SHEET_NAME); if (!existing) ss.insertSheet(CONFIG.STATS_SHEET_NAME); buildDashboard(); } Please continue. Using Tool | Write File /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-apps-script/Sidebar.html View <!DOCTYPE html> <!-- GENSPARK AI AGENT REGISTRY ... refreshStats(); </script> </body> </html> Using Tool | Write File /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-apps-script/ManualEntry.html View <!DOCTYPE html> <!-- GENSPARK AI AGENT REGISTRY ... } </script> </body> </html> Please continue — now the helper functions and the final README: Using Tool | Write File /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-apps-script/Helpers.gs View /** * ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ * GENSPARK AI AGENT REGISTRY — Google Apps Script ... SpreadsheetApp.getUi().alert('✅ Triggers installed! The menu will load automatically on every open.'); logAction('Triggers', 'Installed onOpen and onEdit triggers'); } Please continue. Using Tool | Write File /mnt/user-data/outputs/genspark-apps-script/README.md View # ⚡ Genspark AI Agent Registry — Google Apps Script ## Complete Click-by-Click Installation & Usage Guide ... ## 🔗 WORKS BEST COMBINED WITH CHROME EXTENSION The Chrome Extension (also in your package) automatically scans ALL chats. The Apps Script organizes, enriches, and generates skill codes. **Use both together for maximum coverage.** Please continue. Using Tool | Bash Command cd /mnt/user-data/outputs # Zip the Apps Script package zip -r genspark-apps-script.zip genspark-apps-script/ echo \"=== APP SCRIPT ZIP ===\" ls -lh genspark-apps-script.zip echo \"\" echo \"=== ALL FILES ===\" ls -la genspark-apps-script/ echo \"\" echo \"=== COMBINED MASTER ZIP (both tools) ===\" mkdir -p genspark-agent-toolkit cp genspark-chat-extractor.zip genspark-agent-toolkit/ cp genspark-apps-script.zip genspark-agent-toolkit/ cp genspark-apps-script/README.md genspark-agent-toolkit/APPS_SCRIPT_README.md cp genspark-chat-extractor/README.md genspark-agent-toolkit/CHROME_EXTENSION_README.md zip -r genspark-agent-toolkit-COMPLETE.zip genspark-agent-toolkit/ ls -lh genspark-agent-toolkit-COMPLETE.zip View adding: genspark-apps-script/ (stored 0%) adding: genspark-apps-script/Code.gs (deflated 74%) adding: genspark-apps-script/Dashboard.gs (deflated 70%) ... adding: genspark-agent-toolkit/CHROME_EXTENSION_README.md (deflated 52%) adding: genspark-agent-toolkit/genspark-apps-script.zip (stored 0%) adding: genspark-agent-toolkit/genspark-chat-extractor.zip (stored 0%) -rwxr-xr-x 1 user user 52K Mar  6 08:32 genspark-agent-toolkit-COMPLETE.zip Exit Code: 0 Everything is built and packaged. Here are all your downloads: ⚡ Google Apps Script — Complete Delivery 📦 Your Downloads Package\tWhat's Inside\tDownload Apps Script Only\tAll 6 files for Google Sheets\t⬇️ genspark-apps-script.zip Chrome Extension Only\tBuilt in previous response\t⬇️ genspark-chat-extractor.zip 🏆 COMPLETE TOOLKIT\tBoth tools + both READMEs\t⬇️ genspark-agent-toolkit-COMPLETE.zip 🏗️ Apps Script Architecture (6 Files) File\tRole\tKey Capability Code.gs\tMaster controller\tMenus, sheet setup, CSV import, dialog launchers Parser.gs\tAI brain\t25+ keyword patterns, name/purpose/useCase/step extraction, Claude XML generator Dashboard.gs\tVisualizer\tAuto-stats, type breakdown charts, agent directory table Helpers.gs\tUtilities\tonEdit auto-timestamp, sidebar stats API, JSON export, bulk status update Sidebar.html\tControl panel\t4-tab dark sidebar: Setup / Parse / Add / Import ManualEntry.html\tData entry form\tDropdown of 17 agent types, full form with validation 🚀 Install in 6 Clicks (Full SOP) Step\tWhere\tWhat You Click\tExpected Result 1\tsheets.google.com\tCreate new blank sheet\tEmpty spreadsheet opens 2\tTop menu\tExtensions → Apps Script\tScript editor opens in new tab 3\tLeft panel in editor\t+ → Script (×4 times) / + → HTML (×2 times)\t6 files created 4\tEach file\tPaste contents from package → Ctrl+S\tCode saved per file 5\tYour Google Sheet\tRefresh the page (F5)\t⚡ Agent Registry menu appears 6\tNew menu\t⚡ Agent Registry → Setup All Sheets → Allow\t5 sheets auto-created 🔄 How The Two Tools Work Together Copy Chrome Extension              Google Apps Script ─────────────────             ────────────────────────────── Runs IN your browser          Runs INSIDE Google Sheets Scans ALL chat pages          Parses pasted chat text Exports CSV                ──→ Import CSV tab in sidebar Auto-detects agents           Manual entry for missed agents Generates skill codes         Regenerates + enriches codes ──→ Dashboard shows all stats ──→ Claude Skills sheet for export Best practice: Use the Chrome Extension first to do the bulk scan → Export CSV → Import into the Apps Script sheet for organization, enrichment, and long-term maintenance. Test the Chrome extension on my Genspark chats Show me how to customize the agent keywords Super Agent Hire an AI today Free Today +13 Ultra Speak"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=0007a297-7d5e-4399-9b2d-fcf62514e565","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=0007a297-7d5e-4399-9b2d-fcf62514e565"}]}]}]
